BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-05-05T22:00:00&endDate=2026-05-05T22:59:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nELIZABETH LINE: Bank Holiday Monday 4\, Tuesday 5\, Wednesday 6 and Thursday 7 May\, the 2217 Abbey Wood to Reading train will terminate at Maidenhead. Customers travelling to Twyford and Reading should change at Maidenhead to the 2338 GWR service to Twyford and Reading. At Maidenhead\, connecting westbound GWR trains to Twyford and Reading use Platform 1. For step-free interchange from platform 3 to platform 1\, please use the lift to the main entrance\, and then continue at street level under the railway bridge and up Shoppenhangers Road to the car park. Please ask staff to open the gate to platform 1\, and allow extra time for your journey
DTEND:20260505T225900Z
DTSTART:20260505T220000Z
SUMMARY:Elizabeth line: Reduced Service
UID:38ebc5cc-3fc5-412c-b0f1-f5e0cf5e1fbb@38eb.org
END:VEVENT
